  {
    "eu_id": "EU-0003",
    "kind": "section_text_panel",
    "page": "jiaocaineedrop_5f9c4ab08cac7457e9111a30e4664920607ea2c115a1433d7be98e97e64244ca.pdf_2",
    "primary_id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_5f9c4ab08cac7457e9111a30e4664920607ea2c115a1433d7be98e97e64244ca.pdf_2_2",
    "source": "header_anchor",
    "member_count": 9,
    "elements": [
      {
        "id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_5f9c4ab08cac7457e9111a30e4664920607ea2c115a1433d7be98e97e64244ca.pdf_2_2",
        "observed_type": "title",
        "canon_role": "section_header",
        "text": "An Interview with Dr. Rick Rediske, Program Manager",
        "bbox": [
          0.34186046511627904,
          0.27150415721844295,
          0.6775193798449612,
          0.2854119425547997
        ],
        "order": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_5f9c4ab08cac7457e9111a30e4664920607ea2c115a1433d7be98e97e64244ca.pdf_2_3",
        "observed_type": "list",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "In our advanced research laboratories, WRI conducts sophisticated and comprehensive environmental analyses and research. This information is the foundation that helps us make decisions about living responsibly within our environment.",
        "bbox": [
          0.03565891472868217,
          0.29145880574452004,
          0.25426356589147286,
          0.46863189720332576
        ],
        "order": 4
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_5f9c4ab08cac7457e9111a30e4664920607ea2c115a1433d7be98e97e64244ca.pdf_2_5",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Why is it important for WRI to continue to investigate the presence of chemical contaminates in the environment?",
        "bbox": [
          0.34108527131782945,
          0.2920634920634921,
          0.5976744186046512,
          0.3398337112622827
        ],
        "order": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_5f9c4ab08cac7457e9111a30e4664920607ea2c115a1433d7be98e97e64244ca.pdf_2_11",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "organisms. The laboratory is dedicated exclusively to culturing specimens and testing how toxins affect these organisms.",
        "bbox": [
          0.6372093023255814,
          0.2920634920634921,
          0.9147286821705426,
          0.3404383975812547
        ],
        "order": 6
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_5f9c4ab08cac7457e9111a30e4664920607ea2c115a1433d7be98e97e64244ca.pdf_2_6",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "The testing we do serves two purpos- es. First, it helps define the nature and the extent of a problem or a potential prob- lem. The best means of protecting our water quality is by preventing problems before they occur. That's why we need to continually assess the condition of our environment so we can detect changes that might signal a potential problem.",
        "bbox": [
          0.34108527131782945,
          0.34285714285714286,
          0.6162790697674418,
          0.49040060468631896
        ],
        "order": 7
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_5f9c4ab08cac7457e9111a30e4664920607ea2c115a1433d7be98e97e64244ca.pdf_2_12",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "You completed an extensive investigation of sediment contamination in the Tannery Bay of White Lake in Muskegon County. Can you give us a summary of the results and tell us how this investigation will help clean-up efforts?",
        "bbox": [
          0.6364341085271318,
          0.3585789871504157,
          0.9147286821705426,
          0.4565381708238851
        ],
        "order": 8
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_5f9c4ab08cac7457e9111a30e4664920607ea2c115a1433d7be98e97e64244ca.pdf_2_13",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "The results of the project show that there are adverse ecological effects asso- ciated with the sediment contamination. In addition, mixing and resuspension of the sediments continues to move the con- taminates from Tannery Bay into other parts of White Lake. The identification of these issues has resulted in the Michigan Department of Environmental Quality raising the priority of sediment remediation of Tannery Bay.",
        "bbox": [
          0.6372093023255814,
          0.45895691609977324,
          0.9116279069767442,
          0.6403628117913832
        ],
        "order": 9
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_5f9c4ab08cac7457e9111a30e4664920607ea2c115a1433d7be98e97e64244ca.pdf_2_7",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Second, it provides important informa- tion that will help decision-makers identi- fy what should happen next. Without ade- quate data, those who are working towards change will have a difficult time developing viable solutions.",
        "bbox": [
          0.34186046511627904,
          0.4922146636432351,
          0.6155038759689923,
          0.5907785336356765
        ],
        "order": 10
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_5f9c4ab08cac7457e9111a30e4664920607ea2c115a1433d7be98e97e64244ca.pdf_2_4",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "\"The data we are able to extract from thorough testing procedures provides vital input in decisions that affect our choices and our quality of life.\"",
        "bbox": [
          0.03565891472868217,
          0.5121693121693122,
          0.24651162790697675,
          0.6173847316704459
        ],
        "order": 11
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "eu_id": "EU-0004",
    "kind": "text_cluster_panel",
    "page": "jiaocaineedrop_5f9c4ab08cac7457e9111a30e4664920607ea2c115a1433d7be98e97e64244ca.pdf_2",
